<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sisko's quarters</td></tr>
<tr id="L1"><td><a href="#L1">1</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: We're looking at a picture of a pastoral landscape with some woodland and gently rolling hills.</td></tr>

<tr id="L2"><td><a href="#L2">2</a></td><td>SISKO:  There are a few wild moba trees here, and a creek that runs through the meadows and into the forest.</td></tr>

<tr id="L3"><td><a href="#L3">3</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Sisko is showing the picture to Kasidy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L4"><td><a href="#L4">4</a></td><td>SISKO:  Nice spot, huh?</td></tr>

<tr id="L5"><td><a href="#L5">5</a></td><td>KASIDY:  Bajor, right?</td></tr>

<tr id="L6"><td><a href="#L6">6</a></td><td>SISKO:  The Kendra province, just south of the Yolja river. I was there the other day.</td></tr>

<tr id="L7"><td><a href="#L7">7</a></td><td>KASIDY:  I thought you went to a conference in Rakantha.</td></tr>

<tr id="L8"><td><a href="#L8">8</a></td><td>SISKO:  I did. But afterwards Vedek Oram wanted me to visit his monastery. We took a transport across the mountains. The sun was just going down and the entire valley was shimmering in the light. And I said to myself, this is the place. This is where I'm going to build my house.</td></tr>

<tr id="L9"><td><a href="#L9">9</a></td><td>KASIDY:  I've heard you talk that way before.</td></tr>

<tr id="L10"><td><a href="#L10">10</a></td><td>SISKO:  Oh, no, this is not just talk. As of this morning, all of this land belongs to me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L11"><td><a href="#L11">11</a></td><td>KASIDY:  You're serious.</td></tr>

<tr id="L12"><td><a href="#L12">12</a></td><td>SISKO:  Twelve hecapates. I'm going to start building as soon as the war is over. We'll have a place that we can visit any time we want.</td></tr>

<tr id="L13"><td><a href="#L13">13</a></td><td>KASIDY:  Sounds good to me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L14"><td><a href="#L14">14</a></td><td>SISKO:  Maybe someday I'll retire here.</td></tr>

<tr id="L15"><td><a href="#L15">15</a></td><td>KASIDY:  I could see you now, sitting in your rocking chair, watching the sunset over the mountains every night, wondering where you put your teeth.</td></tr>

<tr id="L16"><td><a href="#L16">16</a></td><td>SISKO:  Just like my great-great grandfather, in the glass next to the chair.</td></tr>

<tr id="L17"><td><a href="#L17">17</a></td><td>KASIDY:  It's funny how thing's turn out, isn't it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L18"><td><a href="#L18">18</a></td><td>SISKO:  What do you mean?</td></tr>

<tr id="L19"><td><a href="#L19">19</a></td><td>KASIDY:  Did you ever think that you would become so attached to Bajor that you'd want to spend the rest of your life there?</td></tr>

<tr id="L20"><td><a href="#L20">20</a></td><td>SISKO:  It wasn't part of the master plan, if that's what you mean. But from the moment I set foot on this station, nothing has turned out the way I imagined it. This was supposed to be just a temporary assignment, but it has become much more than that. I guess I was meant to come here. You see, it's almost like my</td></tr>

<tr id="L21"><td><a href="#L21">21</a></td><td>KASIDY:  Destiny.</td></tr>

<tr id="L22"><td><a href="#L22">22</a></td><td>SISKO:  Destiny, yes.</td></tr>

